# .claudeignore
#
# Paths Claude should skip when answering FEATURE questions about this pipeline.
# These files are generated outputs, build artifacts, caches, logs, or large
# binary/data files whose contents do not change feature behaviour.
#
# Claude Code does not enforce this file automatically — it is a manual
# reference. Claude reads it at session start and avoids globbing/grepping
# inside these paths unless a task explicitly requires it (e.g. debugging a
# specific generated PNG, inspecting raw KSpice CSV).
#
# WHAT *IS* RELEVANT (do NOT add to this list):
#   src/                                   — all Python and C# source
#   Plot_CS_Predictions.py, run.py         — top-level orchestrators
#   data/extracted/KSpiceSystemMap.json    — parsed model definition
#   output/diagrams/SignalMapping.json     — signal-name lookup
#   output/diagrams/TSA_Explicit_Topology.json — wired topology used by plotter
#   output/CS_Identified_Parameters.json   — identification results
#   output/diagrams/TSA_Equations.json     — equation list driving topology
#   ../../TimeSeriesAnalysis-master/       — TSA library reference (Identify*, PidIdentifier, PidController…)
# ===========================================================================

# --- Generated visual outputs (regenerated every visualize phase) ----------
output/validation_plots/
output/diagrams/*.html

# --- Generated CSVs (regenerated every simulate phase) ---------------------
output/CS_Predictions.csv

# --- C# build artifacts ----------------------------------------------------
src/CSharp_Engine/**/bin/
src/CSharp_Engine/**/obj/

# --- Python caches ---------------------------------------------------------
**/__pycache__/
*.pyc

# --- Logs ------------------------------------------------------------------
*.log
build_output*.log

# --- Raw simulation data (large CSVs — content rarely needed for features) -
data/raw/*.csv

# --- IDE / VCS noise -------------------------------------------------------
.vs/
.vscode/
.idea/

# --- External references — read ONLY when the user explicitly asks ---------
# C:/dev/kspice-old/                  — old greybox pipeline
# C:/dev/GREYBOX_PIPELINE_OVERVIEW.md — old pipeline overview document
